{"name":"Ice Maiden's Kiss","permission":{"default":0,"HbC5TWvEu9iEIzyL":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You breathe forth purest cold, freezing foes into glittering statues of ice. You immediately make a Cold Breath attack, as if you had spent 2 Advantage to activate the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.traits.uqGxFOEqeurwkAO3]{Breath} Creature Trait. Ice Maiden&rsquo;s Kiss is a magic missile with a Damage equal to your Toughness Bonus, ignoring armor. If the target&rsquo;s Wounds are reduced to 0 its body freezes and turns into a solid statue made of ice, a grizzly representation of its former self. For every +2 SL you may increase the width of the Breath Attack around the target by +Strength Bonus Yards.</p>\n<p><strong>Lore :</strong> The flows of Ice Magic vary in strength. By Kislev&rsquo;s sites of power, along her leylines, in freezing climates and in the depths of winter, Ice Magic is very strong, granting you a +10 to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)} Tests when casting the Lore of Ice. But in warmer climes, it is far weaker and wanes the closer to the equator and the further from the North one travels. When casting in warmer climates, such as in most of the Empire, it counts as if casting next to a Corrupting Influence, causing a @Table[minormis] on a unit&rsquo;s roll of an 8. If you already have a @Table[minormis], the Miscast becomes a @Table[majormis]. In hotter climates, such as in a desert or jungle, you receive a permanent @Condition[Fatigued] Condition until you relocate to a cooler climate. You may spend a Resolve point to mitigate this Fatigue Condition for one round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Ice","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Toughness Bonus Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"Special","aoe":false},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Instant","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":"TB"},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":6,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":true},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":true,"label":"Increase width of Breath Attack","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"value","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"SL","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false,"additional":"+2"}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/ice-magic.png","effects":[],"_id":"2DO6nDvYhzI9ajKg"}
{"_id":"3x11TmfrdUNvRkgr","name":"Flying Servant","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>With a rug, rope, broom or carpet, you animate an object capable of taking you to great heights. For the duration of the spell, you gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.traits.EO05HX7jql0g605A]{Flight 60} Creature Trait as you ride across the skies on your newly animated servant. The animated object has Wounds and carrying Encumbrance equal to 10 + Willpower Bonus with a Toughness Bonus equal to your Intelligence Bonus. Once the object&rsquo;s Wounds reach 0, it becomes inanimate again, and if you are flying while this happens you fall. For every +2 SL you may increase the Wounds and carrying Encumbrance of the animated object by +Willpower Bonus.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore:</strong>&nbsp;Arcane Spells summoned from the Lore of the Desert tend to summon or shift large amounts of dust and sands upon their targets or shroud the caster in whirling sands like a desert storm. Whenever a spell from the Lore of the Desert is cast upon a target, that target has their Movement reduced by -1 and cannot Charge for the duration of the round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Desert","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Willpower Bonus Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"1","aoe":false},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Fellowship Bonus Hours","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":""},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":6,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":false},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":true,"label":"Increase Wounds and Encumbrance","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"value","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"value","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/desert-magic.png","effects":[]}
{"name":"Permafrost","permission":{"default":0,"HbC5TWvEu9iEIzyL":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You channel mighty flows of cold into the land. A heavy frost immediately crusts over every affected surface turning it into snowy terrain and making movement past Walking speed impossible. After casting, on this round only, anyone affected by the sudden chilling cold must succeed on a <strong>Hard (-20) Endurance Test</strong> or gain a @Condition[Stunned] Condition. After one minute, all water in the area freezes and snow begins to form around the affected area. You are immune to Permafrost.</p>\n<p><strong>Lore :</strong>&nbsp;The flows of Ice Magic vary in strength. By Kislev&rsquo;s sites of power, along her leylines, in freezing climates and in the depths of winter, Ice Magic is very strong, granting you a +10 to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)} Tests when casting the Lore of Ice. But in warmer climes, it is far weaker and wanes the closer to the equator and the further from the North one travels. When casting in warmer climates, such as in most of the Empire, it counts as if casting next to a Corrupting Influence, causing a @Table[minormis] on a unit&rsquo;s roll of an 8. If you already have a @Table[minormis], the Miscast becomes a @Table[majormis]. In hotter climates, such as in a desert or jungle, you receive a permanent @Condition[Fatigued] Condition until you relocate to a cooler climate. You may spend a Resolve point to mitigate this Fatigue Condition for one round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Ice","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"You"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"Toughness Yards","aoe":true},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Toughness Bonus Days","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":""},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":10,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":false},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/ice-magic.png","effects":[],"_id":"4IxkhraDM0cYmEr7"}
{"_id":"7puMQv0T8uM1JNlB","name":"Curse of the Djinn","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>The magician channels the immense power of the Djinn through their own body and lays a terrible curse upon their foe as their energy is sapped and their armor fails to protect them. The target suffers a penalty of &ndash;10 to all Tests, in addition to any other modifiers, and may not spend Fortune points. In addition, any of the target&rsquo;s non-magical weapons and armor begin to fail them as they break, crack and turn to dust on impact from the next time they&rsquo;re struck if the curse is not dispelled.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore:</strong> Arcane Spells summoned from the Lore of the Desert tend to summon or shift large amounts of dust and sands upon their targets or shroud the caster in whirling sands like a desert storm. Whenever a spell from the Lore of the Desert is cast upon a target, that target has their Movement reduced by -1 and cannot Charge for the duration of the round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Desert","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Willpower Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"1","aoe":false},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Intelligence Bonus Days","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":""},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":8,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":false},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/desert-magic.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"8xcqDJycW7O9OOP4","name":"Death Frost","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You call up lethal cold from the land as you grip your target with chilling death. This counts as a magic missile with a Damage of +6 that ignores Toughness Bonus and Armor Points. For every 5 Wounds inflicted, your Target receives +1 @Condition[Stunned] Condition. If the target&rsquo;s Wounds are reduced to 0 its body freezes and turns into a solid statue made of ice, a grizzly representation of its former self.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore :</strong>&nbsp;The flows of Ice Magic vary in strength. By Kislev&rsquo;s sites of power, along her leylines, in freezing climates and in the depths of winter, Ice Magic is very strong, granting you a +10 to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)} Tests when casting the Lore of Ice. But in warmer climes, it is far weaker and wanes the closer to the equator and the further from the North one travels. When casting in warmer climates, such as in most of the Empire, it counts as if casting next to a Corrupting Influence, causing a @Table[minormis] on a unit&rsquo;s roll of an 8. If you already have a @Table[minormis], the Miscast becomes a @Table[majormis]. In hotter climates, such as in a desert or jungle, you receive a permanent @Condition[Fatigued] Condition until you relocate to a cooler climate. You may spend a Resolve point to mitigate this Fatigue Condition for one round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Ice","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Touch"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"1","aoe":false},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Instant","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","