{"name":"Wall of Ice","permission":{"default":0,"HbC5TWvEu9iEIzyL":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You form a wall of snowy ice from the ground. The ice wall is Willpower Bonus yards wide, Intelligence Bonus yards tall and 2 yards deep. For every +2 SL you may extend the length of the ice wall by +Willpower Bonus yards. You may not pass through an area emanating any warmth (living bodies, fire, and similar, as dictated by the GM). The wall blocks line of sight and has TB 5, and 10 Wounds times your Toughness Bonus. Fire deals double Damage to the ice wall.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore :</strong> The flows of Ice Magic vary in strength. By Kislev&rsquo;s sites of power, along her leylines, in freezing climates and in the depths of winter, Ice Magic is very strong, granting you a +10 to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)} Tests when casting the Lore of Ice. But in warmer climes, it is far weaker and wanes the closer to the equator and the further from the North one travels. When casting in warmer climates, such as in most of the Empire, it counts as if casting next to a Corrupting Influence, causing a @Table[minormis] on a unit&rsquo;s roll of an 8. If you already have a @Table[minormis], the Miscast becomes a @Table[majormis]. In hotter climates, such as in a desert or jungle, you receive a permanent @Condition[Fatigued] Condition until you relocate to a cooler climate. You may spend a Resolve point to mitigate this Fatigue Condition for one round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Ice","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Willpower Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"Special","aoe":true},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Willpower Bonus Rounds",