{"_id":"FX7LgkoFvUgp5FZc","name":"Dancing Scimitar","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>The magician summons a swirling, flaming scimitar that attacks their enemies. This spell is a magic missile that deals +8 Damage. Any enemy struck gains +1 @Condition[Ablaze] Condition. Any Undead struck take additional +Intelligence Bonus Damage and are knocked prone. For each +2 SL, the missile may inflict an additional + 1 @Condition[Ablaze]&nbsp;Condition on the target.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore:</strong>&nbsp;Arcane Spells summoned from the Lore of the Desert tend to summon or shift large amounts of dust and sands upon their targets or shroud the caster in whirling sands like a desert storm. Whenever a spell from the Lore of the Desert is cast upon a target, that target has their Movement reduced by -1 and cannot Charge for the duration of the round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Desert","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Willpower Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"1","aoe":false},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Instant","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":"8"},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":6,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":true},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/desert-magic.png","effects":[]}
{"name":"Sandstorm","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You command the desert spirits to engulf your enemies in a swirling cloud of choking sand and dust. Anyone trapped within Sandstorm&rsquo;s radius, besides the caster, receives a -30 penalty to all Perception Tests, cannot see past 4 yards in front of them and cannot use missile weapons as the whirling sands make it impossible to aim and fire properly. For each +2 SL, the caster may make one ally immune to the effects of Sandstorm for the duration the spell is active.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Desert","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Willpower Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"Willpower Yards","aoe":true},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Intelligence Bonus Rounds","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":""},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":10,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":false},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":true,"label":"Make Ally Immune to Spells","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"value","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"value","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/desert-magic.png","effects":[],"_id":"HBcnXlSkCmfpZ7GY"}
{"name":"Ice Sheet","permission":{"default":0,"HbC5TWvEu9iEIzyL":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You glaze an area of the ground in front of you with a thin layer of slippery ice. Those in the area must succeed on a <strong>Difficult (&ndash;10) Athletics Test</strong> every time they attempt to move across it, or they slip and fall, going @Condition[Prone], and losing their Action. A success means the character can act normally but at half Movement.</p>\n<p><strong>Lore :</strong>&nbsp;The flows of Ice Magic vary in strength. By Kislev&rsquo;s sites of power, along her leylines, in freezing climates and in the depths of winter, Ice Magic is very strong, granting you a +10 to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)} Tests when casting the Lore of Ice. But in warmer climes, it is far weaker and wanes the closer to the equator and the further from the North one travels. When casting in warmer climates, such as in most of the Empire, it counts as if casting next to a Corrupting Influence, causing a @Table[minormis] on a unit&rsquo;s roll of an 8. If you already have a @Table[minormis], the Miscast becomes a @Table[majormis]. In hotter climates, such as in a desert or jungle, you receive a permanent @Condition[Fatigued] Condition until you relocate to a cooler climate. You may spend a Resolve point to mitigate this Fatigue Condition for one round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Ice","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Willpower Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"Willpower Bonus Yards","aoe":true},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Willpower minutes","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":""},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":6,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":false},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/ice-magic.png","effects":[],"_id":"HL4p2CRTTshAczbK"}
{"name":"Shoika's Call","permission":{"default":0,"HbC5TWvEu9iEIzyL":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You call out to the Ancient Widow, reminding her of her promises to Khan-Queen Shoika, first Tzarina of Kislev, and cause 20-foot tendrils of ice to erupt from the ground. All creatures in the area has their Movement halved and must succeed a<strong> Challenging (+0) Athletics Test</strong> each round or the tendrils wrap around them dealing SB+4 Damage that ignores armor and count as having the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.traits.KynNUYYKzTMeHrKl]{Constrictor} Creature Trait. The tendrils count as having a Weapon Skill equal to yours and Strength equal to your Intelligence Characteristic.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore :</strong>&nbsp;The flows of Ice Magic vary in strength. By Kislev&rsquo;s sites of power, along her leylines, in freezing climates and in the depths of winter, Ice Magic is very strong, granting you a +10 to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)} Tests when casting the Lore of Ice. But in warmer climes, it is far weaker and wanes the closer to the equator and the further from the North one travels. When casting in warmer climates, such as in most of the Empire, it counts as if casting next to a Corrupting Influence, causing a @Table[minormis] on a unit&rsquo;s roll of an 8. If you already have a @Table[minormis], the Miscast becomes a @Table[majormis]. In hotter climates, such as in a desert or jungle, you receive a permanent @Condition[Fatigued] Condition until you relocate to a cooler climate. You may spend a Resolve point to mitigate this Fatigue Condition for one round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Ice","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Toughness Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"Toughness Yards","aoe":true},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Willpower Bonus Rounds","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":""},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":16,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":false},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/ice-magic.png","effects":[],"_id":"Tcgfdb7iVdo6Dc8i"}
{"_id":"UXHgHKjAUAa27zfc","name":"Hailstorm","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You channel Ice Magic upwards, forming large chunks of ice that fall to the ground with horrifying speed. This counts as a magic missile dealing +Willpower Bonus Damage at the beginning of each round. All targets within the radius take a &ndash;20 penalty to all Ballistic Skill Tests and halve their Movement. While the spell is in effect, the ice witch may attempt a @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} Test and, if successful, may move the Hailstorm 2 yards per SL.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore :</strong>&nbsp;The flows of Ice Magic vary in strength. By Kislev&rsquo;s sites of power, along her leylines, in freezing climates and in the depths of winter, Ice Magic is very strong, granting you a +10 to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)} Tests when casting the Lore of Ice. But in warmer climes, it is far weaker and wanes the closer to the equator and the further from the North one travels. When casting in warmer climates, such as in most of the Empire, it counts as if casting next to a Corrupting Influence, causing a @Table[minormis] on a unit&rsquo;s roll of an 8. If you already have a @Table[minormis], the Miscast becomes a @Table[majormis]. In hotter climates, such as in a desert or jungle, you receive a permanent @Condition[Fatigued] Condition until you relocate to a cooler climate. You may spend a Resolve point to mitigate this Fatigue Condition for one round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Ice","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Toughness Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"Willpower Bonus Yards","aoe":true},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Toughness Bonus Rounds","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":"WPB"},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":7,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":true},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/ice-magic.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Vd1LiC1lzs5JkptN","name":"Sand Blast","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>A blasting sandstorm erupts from the magician&rsquo;s mouth, throwing those who stand before them onto the ground and covering them in sand. This spell is a magic missile that deals +6 Damage ignoring armor. Any target struck gains a @Condition[Blind] Condition and must attempt a <strong>Challenging (+0) Endurance Test</strong> or be knocked @Condition[Prone].</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore:</strong>&nbsp;Arcane Spells summoned from the Lore of the Desert tend to summon or shift large amounts of dust and sands upon their targets or shroud the caster in whirling sands like a desert storm. Whenever a spell from the Lore of the Desert is cast upon a target, that target has their Movement reduced by -1 and cannot Charge for the duration of the round.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore:</strong>&nbsp;Arcane Spells summoned from the Lore of the Desert tend to summon or shift large amounts of dust and sands upon their targets or shroud the caster in whirling sands like a desert storm. Whenever a spell from the Lore of the Desert is cast upon a target, that target has their Movement reduced by -1 and cannot Charge for the duration of the round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Desert","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Willpower Bonus Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"Willpower Bonus Yards","aoe":true},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Instant","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":"6"},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":8,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":true},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/desert-magic.png","effects":[]}
{"name":"Summon Djinn","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You channel through the winds briefly forcing into your service a mighty ally. A <a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom\" data-id=\"pngADezTmQbEm3G9\"> Djinn</a> immediately manifests. Perform an <strong>Opposed Channel/Willpower Test</strong> with the Djinn. If successful, the Djinn will respond to any commands issued by the caster, then vanish once the duration ends. If failed, the Djinn immediately turns on its master and must be destroyed. For every +2 SL you may add an additional Optional Trait for the Djinn prior to its manifestation; however, the Djinn will maintain these Traits even if it turns against you. The element the Djinn is manifested from is determined randomly and gains attributes based on the results. Roll a d10 and refer to the table below for the type of Djinn summoned:</p>\n<table style=\"width: 98.9247%; height: 176px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>Roll</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 80%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Djinn Element:</strong> All Lore Effects apply when casting.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 80%; height: 16px;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom\" data-id=\"BSmye4uGN8FUsHrX\"> Light</a>: Gains the Impact Quality for all physical attacks against Daemons.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 80%; height: 16px;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom\" data-id=\"dU8b6zCqbXH27QuO\"> Metal</a>: Gains +5 Armor Points.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 80%; height: 16px;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom\" data-id=\"YeTtm6QImWKOqKQl\"> Life</a>: Gains the <a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"wfrp4e-core.traits\" data-id=\"SfUUdOGjdYpr3KSR\"> Regenerate</a> Trait.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 80%; height: 16px;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom\" data-id=\"lm1UsTjkTyzcBe70\"> Heavens</a>: Gains the <a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"wfrp4e-core.traits\" data-id=\"uqGxFOEqeurwkAO3\"> Breath</a> +5 Lightning Trait.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">5</td>\n<td style=\"width: 80%; height: 16px;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom\" data-id=\"e7xqZt4FMSAa5X5p\"> Shadow</a>: Gains the <a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"wfrp4e-core.traits\" data-id=\"uqGxFOEqeurwkAO3\"> Breath</a> +5 Smoke Trait.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">6</td>\n<td style=\"width: 80%; height: 16px;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom\" data-id=\"UsLgUwPFs1irOOwi\"> Death</a>: Gains the Impact Quality for all physical attacks against <a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"wfrp4e-core.traits\" data-id=\"PFTD9gDvRWW9uh5g\"> Undead</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">7</td>\n<td style=\"width: 80%; height: 16px;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom\" data-id=\"JOC4NfR16GxRJCFv\"> Fire</a>: Gains the <a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"wfrp4e-core.traits\" data-id=\"uqGxFOEqeurwkAO3\"> Breath</a> +5 Fire Trait.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">8</td>\n<td style=\"width: 80%; height: 16px;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom\" data-id=\"5e9DhxCRsy9WMxx2\"> Beast</a>: Gains the <a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"wfrp4e-core.traits\" data-id=\"yRhhOlt18COq4e1q\"> Frenzy</a> Trait.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 20%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">9</td>\n<td style=\"width: 80%; height: 16px;\"><a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom\" data-id=\"sldvAhi78DJChJ6Q\"> Ice</a>: Gains the <a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"wfrp4e-core.traits\" data-id=\"uqGxFOEqeurwkAO3\"> Breath</a> +5 Frost Trait.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 20%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">10</td>\n<td style=\"width: 80%; height: 16px;\">@Compendium[nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e.bestiary-nom.njHNgkDoYwGtj0mz]{Dhar}: Gains the <a class=\"entity-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"wfrp4e-core.traits\" data-id=\"kJNAY1YRaCy9IgmT\"> Terror (3)</a> Trait.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Desert","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Willpower Bonus Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"Special","aoe":false},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Willpower Bonus Hours","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":""},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":12,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":false},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/desert-magic.png","effects":[],"_id":"XxmlmN89d5RT012Y"}
{"_id":"c0DM4WCtLftKxDPd","name":"Crystal Cloak","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You call forth a swirling, shimmering, ice-laden mist and wrap it around you. Anyone within Toughness Bonus yards of you takes a &ndash;10 penalty to all Weapon Skill, Ballistic Skill and Agility Tests as the cloak&rsquo;s cold seeps into them. Further, anything living trying to attack you in melee combat must pass an <strong>Average (+20) @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance} Test</strong> or lose their Action for next round due to the cloaks intense cold chilling them to the bone. This Test does not apply to creatures with the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.traits.PFTD9gDvRWW9uh5g]{Undead} or @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.traits.v3uzEthcq0JRar0J]{Daemonic} Traits. For each +2 SL, you may increase the difficulty of the Endurance Test by an additional -10 up to a maximum penalty of -50.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore :</strong>&nbsp;The flows of Ice Magic vary in strength. By Kislev&rsquo;s sites of power, along her leylines, in freezing climates and in the depths of winter, Ice Magic is very strong, granting you a +10 to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)} Tests when casting the Lore of Ice. But in warmer climes, it is far weaker and wanes the closer to the equator and the further from the North one travels. When casting in warmer climates, such as in most of the Empire, it counts as if casting next to a Corrupting Influence, causing a @Table[minormis] on a unit&rsquo;s roll of an 8. If you already have a @Table[minormis], the Miscast becomes a @Table[majormis]. In hotter climates, such as in a desert or jungle, you receive a permanent @Condition[Fatigued] Condition until you relocate to a cooler climate. You may spend a Resolve point to mitigate this Fatigue Condition for one round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Ice","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"You"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"You","aoe":false},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Willpower Bonus Rounds","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":""},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":7,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":false},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":true,"label":"Increase Opponent Endurance Test Difficulty","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"value","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"value","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/ice-magic.png","effects":[]}
{"name":"Hawks of Miska","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>By calling upon pacts sealed by the first Khan-Queens, you summon the Hawks of Miska, frozen spirits of fear, hatred, and dread. The icy birds crystallize from the air and swoop around the targets, loosing fearful cries. All creatures in the area must pass a @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.traits.pTorrE0l3VybAbtn]{Fear (1)} Test every round the spell is active or until they fail. For every +2 SL you may increase the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.traits.pTorrE0l3VybAbtn]{Fear} Rating by 1.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore :</strong>&nbsp;The flows of Ice Magic vary in strength. By Kislev&rsquo;s sites of power, along her leylines, in freezing climates and in the depths of winter, Ice Magic is very strong, granting you a +10 to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)} Tests when casting the Lore of Ice. But in warmer climes, it is far weaker and wanes the closer to the equator and the further from the North one travels. When casting in warmer climates, such as in most of the Empire, it counts as if casting next to a Corrupting Influence, causing a @Table[minormis] on a unit&rsquo;s roll of an 8. If you already have a @Table[minormis], the Miscast becomes a @Table[majormis]. In hotter climates, such as in a desert or jungle, you receive a permanent @Condition[Fatigued] Condition until you relocate to a cooler climate. You may spend a Resolve point to mitigate this Fatigue Condition for one round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Ice","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Willpower Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"Willpower Bonus Yards","aoe":true},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Willpower Bonus Rounds","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":""},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":9,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":false},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/ice-magic.png","effects":[],"_id":"c2kGYd5oOCO9XqVR"}
{"_id":"kHqr2B7GahN31JCz","name":"Mirage","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You summon a clone of yourself to fool your enemies, confusing them with your illusory magics. You may create one clone per cast and one additional clone per +2 SL. You will automatically fool anyone without the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.OEjUvJKi0xmBwbS2]{Second Sight} Talent. Those with that Talent must pass a Difficult (&ndash;10) Perception Test to notice the illusion. This does not let them see through the spell. They must dispel it to do so. During combat, illusory clones may attack or defend as if they are real, sharing your Weapon Skill and appropriate Melee Skills, but cannot deal or receive Damage. Clones may still help grant an outnumbering bonus against their enemies. Those engaged with the illusion must attempt a <strong>Hard (-20) Willpower Test</strong> to resist its effects or else treat it as if it is real and act accordingly, regardless if they are aware it&rsquo;s an illusion or not.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore:</strong>&nbsp;Arcane Spells summoned from the Lore of the Desert tend to summon or shift large amounts of dust and sands upon their targets or shroud the caster in whirling sands like a desert storm. Whenever a spell from the Lore of the Desert is cast upon a target, that target has their Movement reduced by -1 and cannot Charge for the duration of the round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Desert","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Willpower Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"Special","aoe":false},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Intelligence Bonus Minutes","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":""},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":8,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":false},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/desert-magic.png","effects":[]}
{"name":"Sun Spear","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Bright beams of burning energy leap from the magician's eyes and scythe through all before them. This is a magic missile with a Damage of +12. It strikes the first creature in its path. If the target suffers any Wounds, also inflict +1 @Condition[Ablaze] Condition, after which the spear continues its path, striking each target in the same manner, but at &ndash;1 Damage each time. If the spear fails to inflict any Wounds, its progress is stopped, and the spell comes to an end. The Sun Spear only inflicts the minimum 1 Wound (see page 236) on the first target it strikes.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Desert","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Willpower Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"Special","aoe":false},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Instant","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":"12"},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":8,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":true},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/desert-magic.png","effects":[],"_id":"lNZX4QYOOBynrt6g"}
{"_id":"mqkBtPUX7NEF0ouV","name":"Frost Blade","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>A sparkling blade of ice forms in your hand, taking any shape you wish. It counts as a magic weapon with a Damage equal to your Willpower Bonus+3. Enemies that lose 5 Wounds or more from each strike gain +1 @Condition[Stunned] Condition. The blade immediately melts away if you let go of it or once the duration ends.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore :</strong>&nbsp;The flows of Ice Magic vary in strength. By Kislev&rsquo;s sites of power, along her leylines, in freezing climates and in the depths of winter, Ice Magic is very strong, granting you a +10 to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)} Tests when casting the Lore of Ice. But in warmer climes, it is far weaker and wanes the closer to the equator and the further from the North one travels. When casting in warmer climates, such as in most of the Empire, it counts as if casting next to a Corrupting Influence, causing a @Table[minormis] on a unit&rsquo;s roll of an 8. If you already have a @Table[minormis], the Miscast becomes a @Table[majormis]. In hotter climates, such as in a desert or jungle, you receive a permanent @Condition[Fatigued] Condition until you relocate to a cooler climate. You may spend a Resolve point to mitigate this Fatigue Condition for one round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Ice","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"You"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"You","aoe":false},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Willpower Bonus Rounds","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":""},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":5,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":false},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/ice-magic.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"mqktfTIQDkgycvwc","name":"Chill","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Your touch leaves a gleaming frost behind. The air in the area drops to freezing temperatures for the duration, making breathe visible and turning water to ice instantly.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore :</strong>&nbsp;The flows of Ice Magic vary in strength. By Kislev&rsquo;s sites of power, along her leylines, in freezing climates and in the depths of winter, Ice Magic is very strong, granting you a +10 to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)} Tests when casting the Lore of Ice. But in warmer climes, it is far weaker and wanes the closer to the equator and the further from the North one travels. When casting in warmer climates, such as in most of the Empire, it counts as if casting next to a Corrupting Influence, causing a @Table[minormis] on a unit&rsquo;s roll of an 8. If you already have a @Table[minormis], the Miscast becomes a @Table[majormis]. In hotter climates, such as in a desert or jungle, you receive a permanent @Condition[Fatigued] Condition until you relocate to a cooler climate. You may spend a Resolve point to mitigate this Fatigue Condition for one round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Ice","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"You"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"You","aoe":false},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Toughness Bonus Hours","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":""},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":4,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":false},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/ice-magic.png","effects":[]}
{"name":"Shardstorm","permission":{"default":0,"HbC5TWvEu9iEIzyL":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You unleash diamond-hard shards of ice at a single target, in an amount of shards equal to your Toughness Bonus. Each shard is a magic missile dealing +3 Damage to a single enemy. For every +2 SL you may summon an additional shard to fire at your target.</p>\n<p><strong>Lore :</strong> The flows of Ice Magic vary in strength. By Kislev&rsquo;s sites of power, along her leylines, in freezing climates and in the depths of winter, Ice Magic is very strong, granting you a +10 to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)} Tests when casting the Lore of Ice. But in warmer climes, it is far weaker and wanes the closer to the equator and the further from the North one travels. When casting in warmer climates, such as in most of the Empire, it counts as if casting next to a Corrupting Influence, causing a @Table[minormis] on a unit&rsquo;s roll of an 8. If you already have a @Table[minormis], the Miscast becomes a @Table[majormis]. In hotter climates, such as in a desert or jungle, you receive a permanent @Condition[Fatigued] Condition until you relocate to a cooler climate. You may spend a Resolve point to mitigate this Fatigue Condition for one round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Ice","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Willpower Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"Special","aoe":false},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Instant","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":"+3"},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":8,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":true},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":true,"label":"Summon Additional Shards","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"value","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"SL","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false,"additional":"+2"}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/ice-magic.png","effects":[],"_id":"nlG5zkUTh1uNTSu2"}
{"_id":"oF0GbqL8w3W49Jus","name":"Quicksand","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>The magician causes the ground to sink beneath the targets as a pit of quicksand appears, slowly bringing them to their doom. Any targets hit by Quicksand have their Movement halved and must roll a <strong>Hard (-20) Athletics Test</strong> or be knocked @Condition[Prone] so long as they remain within the spell&rsquo;s radius. Those affected may retake the test at the end of each subsequent Round to remove the @Condition[Prone] Condition. After the duration ends, the targets must then roll an additional<strong> -20 Agility Test</strong> or be sucked in by the quicksand to their deaths. The target must be a @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.traits.8slW8CJ2oVTxeQ6q]{Size (Large)} creature or smaller. This spell requires sufficient terrain in order to function, such as sand or soil.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore:</strong>&nbsp;Arcane Spells summoned from the Lore of the Desert tend to summon or shift large amounts of dust and sands upon their targets or shroud the caster in whirling sands like a desert storm. Whenever a spell from the Lore of the Desert is cast upon a target, that target has their Movement reduced by -1 and cannot Charge for the duration of the round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Desert","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Willpower Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"Willpower Bonus Yards","aoe":true},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Intelligence Bonus Rounds","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":""},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":10,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":false},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/desert-magic.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"pOql6YVNBt21t13s","name":"Blizzard","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>A swirling flurry of snow and ice rises from the land, freezing and blinding all in its path. Distant targets may require a @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception} Test to see clearly, as dictated by the GM. Those within the radius of the spell take +Willpower Bonus Damage every round, ignoring armor, and reduce their line of sight to only 6 yards. Targets also take a &ndash;20 penalty to their Ballistic Skill and Agility Tests and have their Movement reduced by half. You are immune to Blizzard. For every +2 SL you may increase the Damage of Blizzard by +Willpower Bonus.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore :</strong>&nbsp;The flows of Ice Magic vary in strength. By Kislev&rsquo;s sites of power, along her leylines, in freezing climates and in the depths of winter, Ice Magic is very strong, granting you a +10 to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)} Tests when casting the Lore of Ice. But in warmer climes, it is far weaker and wanes the closer to the equator and the further from the North one travels. When casting in warmer climates, such as in most of the Empire, it counts as if casting next to a Corrupting Influence, causing a @Table[minormis] on a unit&rsquo;s roll of an 8. If you already have a @Table[minormis], the Miscast becomes a @Table[majormis]. In hotter climates, such as in a desert or jungle, you receive a permanent @Condition[Fatigued] Condition until you relocate to a cooler climate. You may spend a Resolve point to mitigate this Fatigue Condition for one round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Ice","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Willpower Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"Willpower Yards","aoe":true},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Toughness Bonus Rounds","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":""},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":12,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":false},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":true,"label":"Increase Blizzard Damage","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"value","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"value","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/ice-magic.png","effects":[]}
{"name":"Winter Walk","permission":{"default":0,"HbC5TWvEu9iEIzyL":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You demand the winter spirits grant you passage. You take no Movement penalty in the snow or on ice and are immune to the negative effects and penalties from cold weather including blizzards during travel.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore :</strong> The flows of Ice Magic vary in strength. By Kislev&rsquo;s sites of power, along her leylines, in freezing climates and in the depths of winter, Ice Magic is very strong, granting you a +10 to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)} Tests when casting the Lore of Ice. But in warmer climes, it is far weaker and wanes the closer to the equator and the further from the North one travels. When casting in warmer climates, such as in most of the Empire, it counts as if casting next to a Corrupting Influence, causing a @Table[minormis] on a unit&rsquo;s roll of an 8. If you already have a @Table[minormis], the Miscast becomes a @Table[majormis]. In hotter climates, such as in a desert or jungle, you receive a permanent @Condition[Fatigued] Condition until you relocate to a cooler climate. You may spend a Resolve point to mitigate this Fatigue Condition for one round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Ice","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"You"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"You","aoe":false},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"1 Day","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":""},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":3,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":false},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/ice-magic.png","effects":[],"_id":"qCuzgwOb45ybYZaQ"}
{"_id":"qgdwGhYIaGYWR6h9","name":"Biting Wind","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You channel mighty flows of magic into a howling gale of cold. This is a magic missile. Anyone between you and your target within 2 yards of the missile is slashed by wind-whipped ice shards dealing +6 damage. In addition, creatures that lost 5 Wounds or more from this spell gain a @Condition[Stunned] Condition and must pass a <strong>Challenging (+0) @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance} Test</strong> or be forced prone from the harsh winds and shards of ice blasting against them.</p>\n<p><strong>Lore :</strong> The flows of Ice Magic vary in strength. By Kislev&rsquo;s sites of power, along her leylines, in freezing climates and in the depths of winter, Ice Magic is very strong, granting you a +10 to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)} Tests when casting the Lore of Ice. But in warmer climes, it is far weaker and wanes the closer to the equator and the further from the North one travels. When casting in warmer climates, such as in most of the Empire, it counts as if casting next to a Corrupting Influence, causing a @Table[minormis] on a unit&rsquo;s roll of an 8. If you already have a @Table[minormis], the Miscast becomes a @Table[majormis]. In hotter climates, such as in a desert or jungle, you receive a permanent @Condition[Fatigued] Condition until you relocate to a cooler climate. You may spend a Resolve point to mitigate this Fatigue Condition for one round.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Ice","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"Willpower Yards"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"1","aoe":false},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Instant","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":"6"},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":10,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":true},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/ice-magic.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"qu4My8KV2Wq9LPRM","name":"Chill Voice","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You speak with the pitiless chill of the Khan-Queens of old. Gain a +20 bonus on all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pKLMbmG3Ivt6mzMf]{Haggle}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}Tests, but take a &ndash;20 penalty to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.0CwV96kTDRF0jUhk]{Entertain} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip} Tests. If speaking to Kislevites, the penalty is ignored.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lore :</strong>&nbsp;The flows of Ice Magic vary in strength. By Kislev&rsquo;s sites of power, along her leylines, in freezing climates and in the depths of winter, Ice Magic is very strong, granting you a +10 to all @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling} and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)} Tests when casting the Lore of Ice. But in warmer climes, it is far weaker and wanes the closer to the equator and the further from the North one travels. When casting in warmer climates, such as in most of the Empire, it counts as if casting next to a Corrupting Influence, causing a @Table[minormis] on a unit&rsquo;s roll of an 8. If you already have a @Table[minormis], the Miscast becomes a @Table[majormis]. In hotter climates, such as in a desert or jungle, you receive a permanent @Condition[Fatigued] Condition until you relocate to a cooler climate. You may spend a Resolve point to mitigate this Fatigue Condition for one round.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"lore":{"type":"String","label":"Lore","value":"Ice","effect":""},"range":{"type":"String","label":"Range","value":"You"},"target":{"type":"String","label":"Target","value":"You","aoe":false},"duration":{"type":"String","label":"Duration","value":"Willpower Bonus Rounds","extendable":false},"damage":{"type":"String","label":"Damage","dice":"","value":""},"cn":{"type":"Number","label":"Casting Number","value":7,"SL":0},"magicMissile":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Magic Missile","value":false},"memorized":{"type":"Boolean","label":"Memorized","value":false},"ingredients":[],"currentIng":{"type":"Number","label":"Ingredient","value":0},"wind":{"value":""},"overcast":{"enabled":false,"label":"","valuePerOvercast":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false},"initial":{"type":"","value":1,"SL":false,"characteristic":"","bonus":false}}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/nations-of-mankind-wfrp4e/icons/spells/ice-magic.png","effects":[]}
